### Components Needed ####
1) Arduino Uno: The microcontroller that acts as the brain of the car.
2) Ultrasonic Sensor (HC-SR04): Measures the distance to objects in front of the car.
3) Relay Module: Controls the power supply to the motors, acting as a switch.
4) DC Motors: Provide the driving force for the car.
5) Motor Power Supply: A battery pack or other power source for the motors.
6) Breadboard and Jumper Wires: For building the circuit.
7) Power Supply for Arduino: Such as a USB cable or a separate battery pack.
